<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In a project proposal I use the namespace feature of PHP 5.3 and tried to integrate it with Zend_Loader.</p>

<p>The goal is to reduce:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
class Some_Rather_Long_Name {}
</code></pre>

<p>to something like</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
namespace Some/Rather/Long;
class Name {}
</code></pre>

<p>which works fine, but needs the following patch to Zend_Loader::loadClass()</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
        // autodiscover the path from the class name
        $file = str_replace(array('_', '\\'), DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR, $class) . '.php';
</code></pre>

<p>It would be great to have this simple addition in the Zend Framework!</p>

